<subSubSection id="02C66578FFFFFFBEFC95992E6C4B7B22" pageId="18" pageNumber="32" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="4A6336F3FFFFFFBEFC95992E6C4B7B22" blockId="18.[831,1437,1385,1604]" pageId="18" pageNumber="32">
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFFFFBEFC95992E6ABD78E3" bold="true" box="[831,944,1386,1410]" pageId="18" pageNumber="32">Remarks:</emphasis>
It is characterized by a slender and compressed test which is ornamented with a few longitudinal costae. 
<emphasis id="78A8EAE1FFFFFFBEFC9599EE6D7C78A3" bold="true" box="[831,1137,1450,1474]" pageId="18" pageNumber="32">Stratigraphic distribution:</emphasis>
It was originally described from the Cretaceous of northern 
<collectingCountry id="32CB7663FFFFFFBEFB1B998F6C197882" box="[1201,1300,1483,1507]" name="Germany" pageId="18" pageNumber="32">Germany</collectingCountry>
(CUSHMAN, 1946), while SAID &amp; KENAWY (1956) recorded this species in the Danian. It is recorded in the Maastrichtian and Paleocene zones of the Esh El Mallaha area.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
